cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with graph drawing techniques and their mathematical formulations.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses iterative numerical approximations used in practical methods for producing graph drawings.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper discusses algebraic formulations and solutions for graph drawing problems.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of numerical approximations in practical methods for producing graph drawings.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses extended computational models that include operations beyond nested radicals or nested roots of low-degree polynomials.
